`‚òÖ Insight ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ`
The action registry uses a **specificity-based matching** pattern: patterns are sorted by number of required traits (descending), so `['MaterialCube', 'HeldBy']` (2 traits) matches before `['MaterialCube', 'Grabbable']` (2 traits) or `['MaterialCube']` (1 trait). A `matchedIds` set prevents duplicate action IDs from less-specific fallback patterns. This is similar to how CSS specificity works ‚Äî more specific selectors win.
